  "texts": [
    "It is implemented using Python, SciPy, and Keras on a system with 6 core i7 5930k 3.5GHz Processor and NVIDIA Pascal TitanX GPU with CUDA 8.0 and CuDNN 6.0.",
    "With great performance and resilience against external test data, this method shows how DL algorithms accurately predicts the AD diagnosis from brain PET imaging investigations.",
    "The DL algorithm's robustness is constrained because of the limited quantity of test data available, and its performance is primarily applicable to the specific clinical distribution found within the ADNI training set.",
    "Al-Khuzaie et al. (2021) proposed a DL methodology for distinguishing between AD patients and healthy people utilizing 2D anatomical slices obtained via MRI.",
    "In contrast to most earlier research, which used a 3D CNN, this work used 2D slices as input data for CNN."
